{\up $}{\footnote\pard\plain{\up $} Playing the Game}
\pard\sa115\sl-275\li115 \b\fs24 Playing the Game\plain\fs24 
\par \pard\sl-235\li115 \fs20 The object of Reversi is to finish the game with more of your red circles on the board than the computer has of blue. (Monochrome monitors will show red as white and blue as black.)
\par \pard\sb75\sl-235\li115 Playing Reversi involves:
\par \pard\sb115\sa35\sl-235\li115 \b Choosing a Skill Level\plain\fs20 
\par \pard\sl-235\li355\fi-235\tx355 *\tab Choose a skill level from the Skill menu.
\par \pard\sb35\sl-195\li355 \fs18 The higher the skill level, the longer the computer spends calculating its moves.
\par \pard\sb115\sa35\sl-235\li115 \b\fs20 Making a Move\plain\fs20 
\par \pard\sl-235\li355\fi-235\tx355 1\tab Move the pointer to a free square.
\par \pard\sb35\sl-195\li355 \fs18 The pointer changes to a cross if you can make a legal move. To make a legal move, at least one of the computer's circles must lie in a horizontal, vertical, or diagonal line between one of your existing circles and the square where you want to move.
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li355\fi-235\tx355 \fs20 2\tab Click the square where you want to move.
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li355 Or press Enter.
\par \pard\sb55\sl-235\li355\fi-235\tx355 3\tab Wait for the computer to move. Then make another move.
\par \pard\sb115\sa35\sl-235\li115 \b Getting a Hint\plain\fs20 
\par \pard\sl-235\li355\fi-235\tx355 *\tab Choose Hint from the Game menu.
\par \pard\sb35\sl-195\li355 \fs18 The hint depends on the skill level selected. At higher skill levels, the computer takes more time before giving a hint. You can accept the suggestion or move elsewhere.
\par \pard\sb115\sa35\sl-235\li115 \b\fs20 Passing Your Turn\plain\fs20 
\par \pard\sl-235\li355\fi-235\tx355 *\tab Choose Pass from the Game menu.
\par \pard\sb35\sl-195\li355 \fs18 You can choose Pass on your first move to force the computer to play first. After that, you cannot choose Pass if you can make a legal move.
\par \pard\sb115\sa35\sl-235\li115 \b\fs20 Starting a New Game\plain\fs20 
\par \pard\sl-235\li355\fi-235\tx355 *\tab Choose New from the Game menu.
